"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872604","Treasury","false","2018-04-06","<p>The Government welcomes the Financial Conduct Authority’s recent discussion paper, ‘Transforming Culture in Financial Services’. The Government has implemented a number of reforms since the financial crisis to improve conduct and encourage a more positive culture in the financial services sector, including through the introduction of the Senior Managers and Certification Regime. The Government will continue to engage with the financial regulators and industry to progress this important issue, including to consider the views raised in this discussion paper.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-04-06T08:58:20.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872604/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872604/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-27","Financial Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department plans to contribute to the debate arising from the Financial Conduct Authority's discussion paper, Transforming culture in Financial Services, published on 12 March 2018.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","134418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872605","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-06","<p>The glorification of terrorists as &quot;martyrs&quot; is a barrier to peace. It is important the Palestinian leadership continue efforts to implement fully the recommendations of the Quartet Report regarding incitement. But we are encouraged by President Abbas and the Palestinian Authority's track record, which shows a commitment to non-violence and a negotiated two-state solution. We have a regular dialogue with both the Palestinian Authority and the Government of Israel in which we reiterate the need for both sides to prepare their populations for peaceful coexistence, including by promoting a more positive portrayal of each other.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-04-06T11:35:54.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872605/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872605/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-27","Palestinians: Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 16 March 2018 to Question 132437, whether the culture of honouring people as martyrs within Palestinian society contributes to regional tensions and extremism and retards progress towards peace between Israel and the Palestinians.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","134419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872606","Department for Education","false","2018-04-05","<p>I refer the hon. Member for Edinburgh North and Leith to the answer I gave on 2 February 2018 to Question 124714 <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2018-01-24/124714/" target="_blank">https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2018-01-24/124714/</a>.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-04-05T16:19:24.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872606/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872606/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872606/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-27","Department for Education: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much money his Department has spent on hospitality in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872607","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-03","<p>Our hospitality expenditure over the last 5 years is set out below. As the majority of our expenditure is overseas this is affected by variations in exchange rates.</p><table><tbody><tr><td>2012-13</td><td>£9,096,057.53</td></tr><tr><td>2013-14</td><td>£9,010,820.18</td></tr><tr><td>2014-15</td><td>£8,177,552.36</td></tr><tr><td>2015-16</td><td>£7,984,424.09</td></tr><tr><td>2016-17</td><td>£9,386,848.70</td></tr></tbody></table>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-04-03T10:44:17.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872607/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872607/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872607/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-27","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much money his Department has spent on hospitality in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872608","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-04-06","<p>Hospitality figures for each of the last five financial years have been provided in the table below.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>2017/18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£16,994.41</p></td><td><p>£35,859.68</p></td><td><p>-£2,954.15</p></td><td><p>£19,280.11</p></td><td><p>£31,786.37</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The figure for 2015-16 is a negative figure due to the reversal of an over accrual from 2014-15.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-04-06T09:31:36.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872608/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872608/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872608/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-27","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how much money his Department has spent on hospitality in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872609","Home Office","false","2018-04-04","<p>‘Hospitality’ expenditure is not separately visible in the Home Office published accounts; the figure is included in ‘Travel, Subsistence and Hospitality’ for the Financial Years requested, refer to the links below:</p><p> </p><p><strong>FY2016/17 page 115:</strong></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/627853/ho_annual_report_and_accounts_2016_2017.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/627853/ho_annual_report_and_accounts_2016_2017.pdf</a></p><p><strong>FY2015/16 - page 132</strong>:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/539638/HO_AR_16_gov.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/539638/HO_AR_16_gov.pdf</a></p><p><strong>FY2014/15 – page 123</strong></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/441282/HO-AR15_web.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/441282/HO-AR15_web.pdf</a></p><p><strong>FY2013/14 – page 109</strong></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/321446/ARA_web_enabled_18_June.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/321446/ARA_web_enabled_18_June.pdf</a></p><p><strong>FY2012/13 – page 131</strong></p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/210660/Annual_Report_and_Accounts_FINAL_updated_logo.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/210660/Annual_Report_and_Accounts_FINAL_updated_logo.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-04-04T10:12:24.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872609/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872609/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872609/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-27","Home Office: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much money his Department has spent on hospitality in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872610","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-04","<p>Information to answer this question is not held at departmental level. A check would have to be made of MoJ HQ and individual premises across the HMCTS and HMPPS estates to obtain the information requested and this would incur a disproportionate cost.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-04-04T15:23:43.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872610/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872610/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872610/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-03-27","Ministry of Justice: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much money his Department has spent on hospitality in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134424"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872611","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-05","<p>The Department’s guidance on hospitality is in accordance with financial procedures and propriety, based on the principles set out in Government Accounting.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Given the nature of this type of expenditure, it is likely that there will be some variation in the levels incurred year on year but in the context of the overall budget managed by the Department, the amounts incurred shown in the table below are less than 0.0001% of overall expenditure.</p><p> </p><p>Expenditure on hospitality in each of the last five years is set out in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015-16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016-17</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hospitality</p></td><td><p>£868</p></td><td><p>£4,220</p></td><td><p>£4,826</p></td><td><p>£3,081</p></td><td><p>£7,164</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-05T14:49:40.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872611/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872611/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872611/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-27","Department for Work and Pensions: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much money her Department has spent on hospitality in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872612","Wales Office","false","2018-04-04","<p>The amount spent hospitality in the Wales Office for the last five financial years is shown below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Spend on Hospitality</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td><td><p>8,439</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015-16</strong></p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2016-17</strong></p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-04-04T16:11:46.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872612/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872612/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872612/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-03-27","Wales Office: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how much money his Department has spent on hospitality in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872613","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-04-16","<p>My Department has spent the following on hospitality in each of the last five years;</p><p> </p><p>2013/14 - £67,492</p><p>2014/15 - £53,769</p><p>2015/16 - £34,841</p><p>2016/17 - £59,755</p><p>2017/18 - £94,085</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-04-16T11:12:03.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872613/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872613/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872613/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-03-27","Northern Ireland Office: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how much money her Department has spent on hospitality in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134427"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872614","Department for International Trade","false","2018-04-09","<p>It is not possible to fully separate the individual costs of hospitality from wider events management costs and venue hire fees. Department policy states that expenditure should be kept as low as possible, compatible with the occasion.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-04-09T15:39:15.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872614/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872614/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872614/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-03-27","Department for International Trade: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how much money his Department has spent on hospitality in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872615","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-29","<p>NHS Improvement is leading work to drive down healthcare associated infections and as part of this have carried out an early assessment of electronic monitoring of hand gel usage. The technology used in some trusts is currently reliant on local data infrastructure and many existing systems would not be able to support it.</p><p> </p><p>It is important to note that automated monitoring of hand gel and soap usage does not address the correct techniques of hand hygiene by healthcare staff. This is important in reducing the spread of infections. NHS Improvement’s work programme for 2018/19 includes a workstream on hand hygiene compliance and monitoring.</p><p> </p><p>We are working with our partners across the health and social care system, including the Care Quality Commission, to ensure that consideration of best practice in hand hygiene policies remains a focus of inspections in acute trusts.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-03-29T15:42:52.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872615/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872615/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872615/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-27","NHS: Hygiene","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of the potential merits of automated electronic monitoring of hand gel usage as a means of collecting more accurate data on hand hygiene compliance.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","134429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872616","Cabinet Office","false","2018-04-05","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-04-05T10:13:12.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872616/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872616/answer","PQ_134430.pdf","PQ_134430.pdf","UKSA Response ","UKSA Response ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872616/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-27","Breast Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many women have been diagnosed with triple negative breast cancer in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","134430"
