"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872639","Treasury","false","2018-03-29","<p>The UK contributes to the EU budget as a whole, not the individual programmes.</p><p>Details of the UK’s contribution to the EU budget can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/european-union-finances-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/european-union-finances-2017</a></p><p>Details of the EU’s spending on programmes can be found here: <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/budget/figures/interactive/index_en.cfm" target="_blank">http://ec.europa.eu/budget/figures/interactive/index_en.cfm</a></p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-03-29T12:04:46.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872639/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872639/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872639/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-27","Galileo System","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what contribution the UK has made to the European Union's Global Satellite Navigation System to date.","false","Biography information for Vicky Ford","Chelmsford","Vicky Ford","134453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872640","House of Commons Commission","false","2018-04-10","<p>The Digital Service is delivering a major investment programme for Parliament’s network; this is addressing issues around speed, resilience and most importantly security when accessing internet based services. As part of this programme, improvements to Wi-Fi availability are being rolled out across the estate by installing additional Wi-Fi access points. Members' areas have been prioritised, with some already completed and the rest (mainly Portcullis House and Palace of Westminster) will be completed by the end of June 2018.</p><p>Further targeted improvements across the estate, forming part of the infrastructure transformation programme, are being scoped including Wi-Fi optimisation and efficiencies. These improvements are scheduled to conclude by February 2019.</p>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2018-04-10T16:27:23.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872640/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872640/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872640/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2018-03-27","Parliamentary Estate: WiFi","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington, representing the House of Commons Commission, what plans the Commission has to improve the (a) availability and (b) speed of Wi-Fi provision on the Parliamentary estate; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","134454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872641","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-16","<p>The law provides for the splitting of benefit payments where the Secretary of State considers it to be in the interests of the claimants or children for whom they are responsible. The Department does not receive representations routinely requesting that payment is split, but of course would readily consider any such requests.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-16T13:51:13.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872641/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872641/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872641/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-27","Social Security Benefits: Automated Credit Transfer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether her Department has made an assessment of the potential merits of requiring claims for a male-female couple to be paid into (a) the woman's bank account and (b) a joint bank account; and what representations her Department received from (i) NGOs and (ii) other organisations on that matter.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","134455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872642","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-03","<p>The Department has made no such estimate. Local authorities are responsible for drawing up and managing their own social housing allocation schemes, within the legislative framework.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-04-03T16:05:01.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872642/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872642/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872642/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-03-27","Social Rented Housing: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will estimate the average first year public sector set-up cost for a new resident in any part of England needing social housing and two school places for children.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","134456"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872643","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-16","<p>National statistics on the number of people living in in-work relative low income are set out in the annual &quot;Households Below Average Income&quot; publication. Average incomes are not available at constituency or ward level in this publication because the survey sample sizes are too small to support the production of robust estimates at this geography. However figures at a regional level are available as a three year rolling average. National figures are available for individual years.</p><p> </p><p>Figures on average incomes by region and for England can be found in the link below, in table 2.5ts, and sets out median and mean incomes before housing costs (BHC) and after housing costs (AHC). Figures for the UK can be found in table 2.1ts, which shows UK income deciles but also the median and mean incomes, both before and after housing costs.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/691966/income-values-and-inequality-measures-hbai-1994-95-2016-17-tables.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/691966/income-values-and-inequality-measures-hbai-1994-95-2016-17-tables.ods</a></p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-16T11:19:32.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872643/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872643/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872643/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-27","Personal Income","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average net weekly household income was for people in (a) Coventry South constituency, (b) the West Midlands, (c) London, (d) the South East, (e) England and (f) the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","134457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872644","Women and Equalities","false","2018-04-16","<p>The LGBT policy team at the Government Equalities Office meet with a range of organisations regularly and will continue to do so as part of their ongoing policy engagement. In 2017, they met with key stakeholders including the LGBT Foundation, Intersex UK, the LGBT Consortium, Stonewall, GIRES Gendered Intelligence and the Commonwealth Equality Network.</p><p>The UK has a proud record of promoting equality for LGBT people, including introducing marriage for same-sex couples. We continue to be recognised as one of the most progressive countries in Europe for LGBT rights by ILGA-Europe. Meeting with LGBT+ organisations ensures that we continue to be at the forefront of progressing LGBT rights in this country.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-04-16T16:39:37.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872644/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872644/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-03-27","LGBT People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what meetings her Department held with LGBT+ organisations in 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","134458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872645","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-16","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-04-16T15:56:59.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872645/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872645/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-27","Maternity Services: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what the take-up rate for six week post-partum examinations for women in (a) the West Midlands and (b) Coventry was in 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","134459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872646","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-16","<p>As at August 2017, the most recent date for which figures are available, there were 2,580 women in Coventry and 56,305 women in West Midlands aged between 60 and 65 years of age (inclusive) in receipt of State Pension. The average weekly amount received by these women was £141.29 in Coventry and £139.93 in West Midlands. Of these, 2,331 in Coventry and 50,784 in the West Midlands received a State Pension based on their own National Insurance contributions; either a Category A pension under the pre-2016 system, or from April 2016 under the new State Pension (nSP).</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Please note that these statistics are publically available via DWP’s dissemination tool Stat-Xplore: <a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/jsf/login.xhtml" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/jsf/login.xhtml</a></p><p> </p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2018-04-16T11:22:35.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872646/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872646/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872646/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-27","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many women aged between 60 and 65 are in receipt of the state pension; the level at which that state pension is paid; and how many women aged between 60 and 65 only receive their National Insurance contributions in (a) Coventry and (b) West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","134460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872647","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-05","<p>The average annual rent charged for accommodation properties rented to non-military personnel living in Ministry of Defence owned properties is £10,944.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-04-05T15:42:11.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872647/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872647/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-27","Ministry of Defence: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 16 March 2018 to Question 131729, on Ministry of Defence; buildings, what the average annual rent charged for those properties was.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","134461"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872648","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-05","<p>Between January 2016 and January 2017, non-military personnel were accommodated for varying periods of time in County Antrim, County Down, Devon, Edinburgh, Fife, Hants and Warwickshire.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-04-05T15:40:31.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872648/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872648/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-27","Ministry of Defence: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 26 February 2018 to Question 131729, on Ministry of Defence: Buildings, the location of the accommodation properties owned by his Department which were rented to non-military personnel between January 2016 and January 2017.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","134462"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872649","Treasury","false","2018-03-29","<p>The UK contributes to the EU budget as a whole, not the individual programmes.</p><p>Details of the UK’s contribution to the EU budget can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/european-union-finances-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/european-union-finances-2017</a></p><p>Details of the EU’s spending on programmes can be found here: <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/budget/figures/interactive/index_en.cfm" target="_blank">http://ec.europa.eu/budget/figures/interactive/index_en.cfm</a></p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-03-29T12:03:14.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872649/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872649/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-27","Copernicus Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what contribution the UK has made to the Copernicus Programme to date.","false","Biography information for Vicky Ford","Chelmsford","Vicky Ford","134463"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872650","Department for Education","false","2018-04-16","<p>The majority of School Efficiency Advisers (SEAs) are practising school business professionals working in the sector. Payment for their deployments as SEAs will go directly to the school or academy trust that employs them.</p><p>These advisers will not be paid to advise the school or academy trust that already employs them, but will be deployed to advise other schools and trusts.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-04-16T11:14:18.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872650/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872650/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-27","Schools: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether payments for school efficiency advisers who are already employed as school business professionals will be made to the school that employs them; and whether such advisers will be paid to advise the school that already employs those advisers.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","134464"
