"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872250","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-29","<p>We regularly engage with the Cabinet on EU exit, including on the agreement to the implementation period. The Government does not comment on internal Cabinet discussions.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-03-29T12:25:43.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872250/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872250/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-03-26","Fisheries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether he consulted the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs before concluding the deal on fisheries on 19 March 2018.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","134164"
